As of the [[census]] of 2010, there were 109 people, 51 households, and 35 families residing in the CDP. There were 92 housing units. The racial makeup of the CDP was 89.0% [[Race (U.S. census)|White]], 1.8% [[Race (U.S. census)|Native American]], 6.4% [[race (U.S. census)|some other race]], and 2.8% from two or more races. 18.3% of the population were [[Race (U.S. census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (U.S. census)|Latino]] of any race.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3255400| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212162855/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3255400| url-status=dead| archive-date=February 12, 2020| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (DP-1): Paradise Valley CDP, Nevada| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=January 24, 2013}}</ref>

